WEBVTT

00:13.458 --> 00:14.750
PACEY?

00:16.792 --> 00:17.834
I THOUGHT THAT
WAS YOU OUT HERE.

00:17.834 --> 00:19.041
WERE YOU EVER
GOING TO COME IN?

00:19.041 --> 00:21.333
I FORGOT YOU GUYS
DON'T LOCK YOUR DOORS.

00:21.333 --> 00:23.834
YEAH, WELL,
ACTUALLY WE'RE GOING
TO HAVE TO START NOW

00:23.834 --> 00:25.125
THAT I GOT ALL
THIS FILM EQUIPMENT
IN HERE.

00:25.125 --> 00:28.250
COME ON INSIDE.
THERE'S SOMETHING
I WANT TO SHOW YOU.

00:28.250 --> 00:29.625
YOU OK?

00:29.625 --> 00:32.208
YEAH.

00:32.208 --> 00:33.333
YEAH.

00:33.333 --> 00:34.750
I--I WENT OUT AFTER WORK
WITH A COUPLE OF GUYS.

00:34.750 --> 00:37.208
WE GOT A LITTLE CAVEMAN.

00:37.208 --> 00:38.708
AH.

00:38.708 --> 00:40.166
BUT I'D LOVE TO SEE
WHAT YOU GOT GOING.

00:49.834 --> 00:51.125
Pacey: WOW.

00:54.792 --> 00:57.959
IT'S PRETTY CRAZY, HUH?

00:57.959 --> 01:00.083
TOOK ME FOREVER.
I WANT TO MAKE SURE
EVERYTHING IS PERFECT.

01:01.583 --> 01:04.625
WHAT DO YOU THINK?
YOU'RE THE FIRST PERSON
WHO'S SEEN IT.

01:08.083 --> 01:10.166
WELL, I WOULD SAY
THAT THIS OFFICIALLY

01:10.166 --> 01:12.125
MAKES YOU THE KING
OF PROCRASTINATION.

01:12.125 --> 01:14.583
NO, NO, NO. WE'RE GOING
TO SHOOT IN HERE.

01:14.583 --> 01:16.750
I KNOW IT'S TIGHT,
BUT I FIGURED OUT A WAY
TO MAKE THE CAMERA FIT.

01:16.750 --> 01:18.750
AND BY SAVING MONEY
ON LOCATIONS,

01:18.750 --> 01:20.291
WE CAN AFFORD TO GO
ALL OUT ON EVERYTHING ELSE.

01:20.291 --> 01:21.917
REALLY?
YEAH.

01:21.917 --> 01:23.375
I GOT 3 CREDIT CARDS
IN THE MAIL LAST WEEK,

01:23.375 --> 01:25.000
MAXED THEM OUT
IN, LIKE, A DAY.

01:25.000 --> 01:26.417
GOT LIGHTS, CAMERAS,
THIS AWESOME SOUND EQUIPMENT.

01:26.417 --> 01:30.583
I'M GOING COMPLETELY
OVERBOARD, BUT I DON'T CARE.

01:30.583 --> 01:34.375
I'M TALKING A MILE A MINUTE.
I HAVEN'T EVEN ASKED YOU
WHAT BROUGHT YOU TO CAPESIDE.

01:39.583 --> 01:41.750
(PACEY SIGHS)

01:41.750 --> 01:43.583
MAN. HA!

01:43.583 --> 01:46.625
BEING IN THIS ROOM,
IT JUST TAKES ME BACK
TO A WHOLE OTHER ERA.

01:46.625 --> 01:50.834
WHEN THE FUTURE
WAS A CLEAN SLATE
FOR ALL OF US, YOU KNOW?

01:50.834 --> 01:53.417
WELL, THE ROOM MAY HAVE
GONE BACK IN TIME,

01:53.417 --> 01:56.417
BUT I THINK
YOU AND I HAVE MOVED
AHEAD RATHER NICELY.

01:56.417 --> 01:58.250
IT'S ABOUT ALL THE OBSTACLES
WE WENT THROUGH
WHEN WE WERE KIDS.

01:58.250 --> 01:59.417
WE BOTH ENDED UP DOING
EXACTLY WHAT WE WANTED TO DO.

01:59.417 --> 02:01.625
WELL, THERE WAS THAT
BRIEF PERIOD OF TIME

02:01.625 --> 02:03.000
I TOYED WITH
THE IDEA OF BEING
A RODEO CLOWN,

02:03.000 --> 02:05.917
BUT I GUESS THIS'LL DO.
HEH HEH.

02:05.917 --> 02:07.291
BUT YOU MADE SOMETHING
OF YOURSELF, PACE,

02:07.291 --> 02:08.917
AND NOW YOU'RE MAKING
SOMETHING OUT OF ME.

02:08.917 --> 02:10.708
I--I DON'T KNOW THAT
YOU SHOULD GO THAT FAR.

02:10.708 --> 02:12.125
I MEAN, YOU HAD DONE
THIS BY YOURSELF. RIGHT?

02:12.125 --> 02:16.125
EVEN IF YOU HAD NOTHING,
THIS WOULD...

02:16.125 --> 02:17.834
I'M NOT...I'M SAY--
YOU'RE NOT HEARING ME, MAN.

02:17.834 --> 02:18.333
I'M...

02:21.375 --> 02:22.583
I'M TRYING TO THANK YOU.

02:22.583 --> 02:23.625
WELL, YOU'RE WELCOME,
I GUESS, BUT, COME ON,

02:23.625 --> 02:26.291
DAWSON, I MEAN, WE ALL
KNEW YOU'D DO THIS.

02:26.291 --> 02:28.458
THIS WAS YOUR DREAM.
YOU JUST...

02:28.458 --> 02:29.041
NEEDED TO TAKE
A LITTLE TRIP DOWN
MEMORY LANE, RIGHT?

02:29.041 --> 02:31.125
YEAH, I NEEDED THAT

02:31.125 --> 02:33.750
AND A VERY FINANCIALLY SAVVY
ASSOCIATE PRODUCER.

02:35.041 --> 02:37.750
I'M GIVING YOU CREDIT
ON THE FILM.

02:37.750 --> 02:39.959
SO...

02:39.959 --> 02:41.375
YOU'RE PART OF THIS NOW.

02:43.125 --> 02:45.458
SO, WELCOME TO HOLLYWOOD,

02:45.458 --> 02:46.291
WHERE PEOPLE
HAVE MEANINGLESS TITLES

02:46.291 --> 02:49.458
FOR NOT EVEN
SHOWING UP ON SET.

02:49.458 --> 02:52.458
I'M SORRY. WHAT IS IT THAT
YOU WANTED TO TALK ABOUT?

02:57.166 --> 02:58.834
UH, IT WAS, UH...

02:58.834 --> 03:01.291
JUST, UH, AS YOUR
ASSOCIATE PRODUCER,

03:01.291 --> 03:05.667
I DO HAVE SOME CONCERNS
ABOUT THE CASTING.

03:05.667 --> 03:07.083
PARTICULARLY
THE ROLE OF PACEY,

03:07.083 --> 03:10.000
WHICH I FEEL
HAS SOME FAIRLY
LARGE SHOES TO FILL.

03:10.000 --> 03:12.375
YOU'RE GOING TO LET
ALL THIS POWER GO STRAIGHT
TO YOUR HEAD, AREN'T YOU?

03:12.375 --> 03:15.166
YEAH, I GOT TO ENJOY IT
WHILE I CAN, RIGHT?

03:15.166 --> 03:18.000
LET ME SHOW YOU
THESE HEADSHOTS.

03:18.000 --> 03:19.125
I GOTTA TELL YA,
I DON'T THINK
THESE AMATEURS KNOW

03:19.125 --> 03:20.458
WHAT THEY'RE GETTING INTO.

03:22.458 --> 03:24.333
NO.

03:24.333 --> 03:25.291
SOMEBODY OUGHT
TO WARN 'EM.

04:15.708 --> 04:16.750
THANK YOU.

04:41.083 --> 04:42.583
(RINGS DOORBELL)

04:52.125 --> 04:54.583
DID YOU GET A HAIRCUT?

04:54.583 --> 04:57.458
UH...NO.

04:57.458 --> 04:58.625
5 INCHES OF BLOND
JUST FELL OFF.

04:58.625 --> 05:00.291
IT WAS REALLY
THE DAMNEDEST THING.

05:00.291 --> 05:02.959
IT'S--IT'S VERY FRENCH.

05:02.959 --> 05:05.208
UM, COME IN.
UH, THE CAB'S GONE,

05:05.208 --> 05:07.333
SO--SO ARE YOUR HOPES
OF LEAVING.

05:07.333 --> 05:09.208
JENNY, PLEASE.

05:14.917 --> 05:16.417
THANK YOU.

05:23.041 --> 05:26.166
YOU LOOK GOOD, MOM.

05:26.166 --> 05:28.542
NOT AS UPPER EAST SIDEY.

05:28.542 --> 05:30.291
I THINK THAT DIVORCE
MUST SUIT YOU.

05:30.291 --> 05:33.625
HMM. A LOT BETTER THAN
MARRIAGE, THAT'S FOR SURE.

05:33.625 --> 05:36.542
Grams: JENNIFER,
DID YOU GET THE DOOR?

05:38.750 --> 05:41.458
HELEN.

05:44.583 --> 05:46.000
HELLO.

05:46.000 --> 05:47.333
GOOD START.

05:47.333 --> 05:49.333
WELL, WHAT--WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

05:49.333 --> 05:52.000
JEN ASKED ME TO COME.

05:52.000 --> 05:54.166
I WAS SO SHOCKED,
I COULD HARDLY SAY NO.

05:54.166 --> 05:56.166
I CAN IMAGINE.

05:56.166 --> 05:58.792
I'LL JUST--CAN I TAKE
MY BAG UPSTAIRS?

05:58.792 --> 06:00.667
OH, OF COURSE.
UH, YOU GO ON UP,

06:00.667 --> 06:03.000
AND I'LL--I'LL
COME UP IN A MINUTE
AND GET YOU SETTLED.

06:03.000 --> 06:04.000
FINE.

06:11.041 --> 06:13.375
JENNIFER.
(STAMMERS)

06:13.375 --> 06:14.917
I KNOW, I KNOW,
I KNOW, I KNOW.

06:14.917 --> 06:16.250
YOU'RE--YOU'RE WORRIED
THAT WE'RE NOT GOING TO HAVE

06:16.250 --> 06:17.542
ENOUGH FOOD
FOR DINNER TONIGHT,

06:17.542 --> 06:19.333
BUT I'VE ACTUALLY
ALREADY TAKEN CARE OF THAT.

06:19.333 --> 06:22.041
JENNIFER, JUST DON'T PULL
YOUR SPEED-TALKING
TECHNIQUE ON ME.

06:22.041 --> 06:24.542
YOU HAD NO RIGHT TO INVITE
THAT WOMAN INTO MY HOUSE.

06:24.542 --> 06:25.542
THAT WO--
WILL YOU CALM DOWN

06:25.542 --> 06:27.875
AND REMEMBER
THAT WE'RE ALL RELATED?

06:27.875 --> 06:29.125
NO, I SPECIFICALLY TOLD YOU

06:29.125 --> 06:32.166
I DID NOT WANT HELEN
TO KNOW THAT I HAD CANCER.

06:32.166 --> 06:33.208
CANCER?

06:34.959 --> 06:37.291
THE POINT IS,
IT IS MY BUSINESS

06:37.291 --> 06:39.041
TO DISPENSE WITH
IN MY OWN TIME,

06:39.041 --> 06:42.041
AND YOU HAD SOME NERVE
TO TAKE IT UPON YOURSELF
TO TELL HER.

06:42.041 --> 06:45.208
I DIDN'T TELL HER.

06:45.208 --> 06:46.542
YOU WILL.

06:46.542 --> 06:48.083
OH.

06:48.083 --> 06:49.708
LOOK, I DON'T THINK
THAT SHE'S ANY FRIGGIN'
MARY POPPINS, MYSELF,

06:49.708 --> 06:52.750
BUT I THINK
THAT SHE DESERVES
TO BE IN THE LOOP,

06:52.750 --> 06:54.750
AND I CAN'T DO THIS ALONE.

06:59.250 --> 07:00.750
I LOVE YOU.

07:10.375 --> 07:13.083
DOES SHE ACTUALLY
RUN IN THESE?

07:13.083 --> 07:14.166
I DON'T KNOW,
I GUESS.

07:14.166 --> 07:17.667
(STRUMS GUITAR)

07:17.667 --> 07:20.250
OH, OK, GROSS.

07:20.250 --> 07:21.750
NO, GROSS.

07:21.750 --> 07:25.458
GOD, CAN'T YOU JUST
PATRONIZE INTERNET PORN
LIKE A NORMAL PERSON?

07:25.458 --> 07:27.458
MUST YOU GO ROOTING AROUND
IN MY ROOMMATE'S SWEATS

07:27.458 --> 07:28.583
LIKE THE HOMELESS MAN
YOU PRETEND TO BE?

07:28.583 --> 07:31.250
MY MOM WAS
SO RIGHT ABOUT YOU.

07:31.250 --> 07:34.417
THIS HOITY-TOITY SCHOOL
HAS MADE YOU SO UPTIGHT.

07:34.417 --> 07:36.875
YOUR MOM THINKS
I'M UPTIGHT?

07:36.875 --> 07:39.291
I MAY HAVE
SOME IN YOUR SIZE
IF YOU WANT ME TO LOOK.

07:39.291 --> 07:41.959
THESE'LL DO JUST FINE.

07:41.959 --> 07:43.333
I'M JOEY.

07:43.333 --> 07:45.708
AH, THE ROOMMATE.
WE FINALLY MEET.

07:45.708 --> 07:48.291
COULD YOU PLEASE STEP
AWAY FROM THE CLOTHES?

07:48.291 --> 07:50.291
SLOWLY. AND KEEP YOUR HANDS
WHERE I CAN SEE THEM.

07:50.291 --> 07:53.542
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

07:53.542 --> 07:55.333
JACK IS HERE TO MEET
WITH THE DEAN

07:55.333 --> 07:56.208
TO DISCUSS IF WORTHINGTON
IS RIGHT FOR HIM

07:56.208 --> 07:58.291
OR SOME SUCH HOO-HA.

07:58.291 --> 08:00.458
RIGHT FOR YOU?

08:00.458 --> 08:02.708
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY
PEOPLE WOULD KILL
TO COME TO THIS SCHOOL?

08:02.708 --> 08:04.542
I MEAN,
I SPENT MY ENTIRE
HIGH-SCHOOL CAREER

08:04.542 --> 08:06.208
JUST TRYING TO GET
AN INTERVIEW HERE.

08:06.208 --> 08:08.625
YOU JUST--
IF IT'S RIGHT FOR YOU?

08:08.625 --> 08:09.917
YOU'RE TURNING
A LITTLE RED.

08:09.917 --> 08:11.041
NOW I KNOW THAT
THIS IS NEW TO YOU,

08:11.041 --> 08:14.166
BUT BEHOLD THE WRATH
OF THE HOLLYWOOD OFFSPRING.

08:14.166 --> 08:16.250
BUT JACK'S A SMART GUY,
AREN'T YOU, JACK?

08:16.250 --> 08:18.959
I'M SMART ENOUGH TO KNOW
IF MY INTEGRITY
IS BEING QUESTIONED

08:18.959 --> 08:21.083
BY A COUPLE
OF UPTIGHT WENCHES.

08:21.083 --> 08:22.333
YEAH, OK.
YOU KNOW WHAT?

08:22.333 --> 08:24.000
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO CHANGE THE T-SHIRT.

08:24.000 --> 08:26.291
SO WHY DON'T YOU BE
A GOOD BOY AND GO
ROOT AROUND IN YOUR SATCHEL,

08:26.291 --> 08:28.000
BECAUSE JOEY AND I
HAVE TO BOND.

08:28.000 --> 08:29.375
I'LL WATCH
FROM A SAFE DISTANCE.

08:31.166 --> 08:33.500
(SIGHS) JOEY.
AUDREY.

08:33.500 --> 08:36.500
I FEEL A LIFETIME MOMENT
COMING ON.

08:36.500 --> 08:37.542
IT'S NOT LIKE
WE'RE NEVER GOING

08:37.542 --> 08:39.166
TO SEE
EACH OTHER AGAIN.

08:39.166 --> 08:41.332
I KNOW, BUT...

08:41.332 --> 08:43.291
OUR TIME IN THIS
PARTICULAR ROOM IS OVER.

08:43.291 --> 08:46.667
ANYWAY, THE POINT IS THIS--

08:46.667 --> 08:49.834
I LOVE YOU VERY MUCH,
JOEY POTTER.

08:49.834 --> 08:52.667
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

08:54.166 --> 08:56.250
SO MUCH SO, IN FACT,

08:56.250 --> 08:58.667
THAT I COULD NOT LEAVE YOU
WITHOUT A PARTING GIFT.

08:58.667 --> 09:02.250
YOU KNOW, SOMETHING FOR
THOSE LONELY SUMMER NIGHTS.

09:02.250 --> 09:03.542
UH, YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE,
AUDREY.

09:03.542 --> 09:05.333
I DIDN'T...

09:05.333 --> 09:06.959
YOU REALLY
SHOULDN'T HAVE.

09:06.959 --> 09:09.625
AUDREY, I HATE
THIS HIDEOUS EYESORE.

09:09.625 --> 09:11.708
I KNOW! WHICH IS WHY
YOU MUST CARRY IT WITH YOU

09:11.708 --> 09:14.917
ON ALL OF YOUR TRAVELS,
BECAUSE, LIKE ME,

09:14.917 --> 09:17.291
IT SEEMS HARSH
AND OVERWHELMING AT FIRST,

09:17.291 --> 09:19.542
BUT ONCE YOU GIVE IN
TO ITS DELICIOUS COMFORT,

09:19.542 --> 09:22.542
YOU WILL FIND THAT YOU
CANNOT LIVE WITHOUT IT.

09:22.542 --> 09:24.041
YOU KNOW
WHAT I'VE REALIZED

09:24.041 --> 09:26.875
IN OUR TENURE TOGETHER?

09:26.875 --> 09:29.041
THAT I'VE NEVER
REALLY HAD A GIRLFRIEND,

09:29.041 --> 09:30.792
NOT A GOOD ONE...

09:30.792 --> 09:33.667
AND NOBODY LIKE YOU.

09:34.208 --> 09:35.708
OH, JOEY.

09:41.542 --> 09:43.250
UH, OK, JACK,
WHAT'S NEXT?

09:43.250 --> 09:46.917
UH, TOMATOES.

09:46.917 --> 09:50.000
SINCE, UM--SINCE WHEN DO YOU
KNOW HOW TO COOK, ANYWAY?

09:50.000 --> 09:51.250
OH, COME ON.
HOW HARD CAN IT BE?

09:51.250 --> 09:53.417
I CAN READ, CAN'T I?

09:53.417 --> 09:54.417
I'M JUST SORRY
I WON'T BE THERE

09:54.417 --> 09:55.792
TO TEST
YOUR CULINARY SKILLS.

09:55.792 --> 09:57.000
YOU'RE COMING.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.250
NO. I'M NOT FACING
MY MOTHER WITHOUT YOU.

09:59.250 --> 10:00.250
WHICH IS EVEN
MORE SHOCKING

10:00.250 --> 10:01.250
THAN THE WHOLE
COOKING THING.

10:01.250 --> 10:02.875
W-WHY IS SHE IN TOWN?

10:02.875 --> 10:03.917
BECAUSE I CALLED HER,
ALL RIGHT.

10:03.917 --> 10:05.583
IT'S--IT'S A LONG STORY.

10:05.583 --> 10:06.959
I'M SURE IT'LL ALL
UNFOLD JUST BEAUTIFULLY
THIS EVENING,

10:06.959 --> 10:08.750
WHICH IS WHY
I NEED YOU THERE
FOR MORAL SUPPORT, OK?

10:08.750 --> 10:12.417
ISN'T C.J. TYPICALLY,
YOU KNOW, THE MORAL PART

10:12.417 --> 10:15.041
OF THE WHOLE,
YOU KNOW...EQUATION.

10:15.041 --> 10:16.792
LOOK, I JUST NEED
THE WHOLE GAMUT

10:16.792 --> 10:18.708
OF BOY POWER
THIS EVENING, OK?

10:18.708 --> 10:20.583
WHICH IS WHY
I DON'T WANT TO BE
THERE FOR THE WHOLE,

10:20.583 --> 10:22.250
YOU KNOW,
MEET THE BOYFRIEND THING.

10:22.250 --> 10:24.083
IT'S REALLY NOT,
LIKE, A WHOLE MEET
THE BOYFRIEND THING.

10:24.083 --> 10:27.333
I MEAN, IT--IT IS,
BUT THAT'S NOT ITS
EXPRESS PURPOSE, OK?

10:27.333 --> 10:30.750
EXACTLY. IT'S MORE
LIKE A, YOU KNOW,
"GOOD-BYE, C.J." TYPE OF NIGHT,

10:30.750 --> 10:32.625
'CAUSE HE'S GOING
TO NEW YORK TOMORROW, RIGHT,

10:32.625 --> 10:33.917
FOR THE WHOLE GRAD THING?

10:33.917 --> 10:36.250
YEAH, YEAH, YES,
HE IS, BUT I'M SURE

10:36.250 --> 10:38.250
THAT WE'LL HAVE PLENTY
OF TIME TO STARE INTO
EACH OTHER'S EYES

10:38.250 --> 10:39.708
AND PONTIFICATE ON WHAT
WE MEAN TO EACH OTHER.

10:39.708 --> 10:40.792
I JUST NEED TO TAKE CARE
OF A COUPLE OF THINGS FIRST.

10:40.792 --> 10:43.667
STRING BEANS.
I NEED STRING BEANS.

12:28.375 --> 12:30.583
GO AHEAD.

13:26.333 --> 13:28.708
IT'S PERFECT.

13:28.708 --> 13:32.041
YOUR EYE FOR DETAIL
IS CREEPY.

13:32.041 --> 13:34.667
THERE'S NO WAY
I'M GOING TO GET
IN THAT CLOSET AND PLAY E.T.,

13:34.667 --> 13:36.208
BUT ASIDE FROM THAT...

13:38.125 --> 13:40.000
IT'S PERFECT.

13:40.000 --> 13:43.708
NOW THAT YOU'RE HERE,
IT'S JUST ABOUT RIGHT.

13:48.041 --> 13:53.166
BUT YOU DO SEEM TO BE
QUITE WELL, HELEN.

13:53.166 --> 13:55.166
YOU, TOO, MOTHER.

13:55.166 --> 13:57.792
DID YOU CHANGE
YOUR HAIR?

13:57.792 --> 14:00.166
MAYBE
A LITTLE MORE GRAY.

14:00.166 --> 14:00.834
JENNIFER'S CHANGED
HER HAIR.

14:00.834 --> 14:02.875
DID YOU NOTICE?
MM.

14:02.875 --> 14:05.625
WE'VE ACTUALLY ALREADY
HAD A DISCUSSION ABOUT THAT.

14:07.959 --> 14:11.583
I HAVE HONEY ON MY HANDS.
UM, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

14:11.583 --> 14:13.458
WHY DON'T YOU TWO
TRY TO FIND A TOPIC

14:13.458 --> 14:16.667
THAT IS MORE PROBING
THAN CURRENT HAIRSTYLES

14:16.667 --> 14:17.917
OR--OR WEATHER PATTERNS?

14:17.917 --> 14:19.166
AND I'LL GO WASH UP, OK?

14:22.667 --> 14:23.959
(WHISPERING)
That means you.

14:32.166 --> 14:35.041
IT SHOULDN'T BE
THIS DIFFICULT, I SUPPOSE,

14:35.041 --> 14:39.125
MAKING CONVERSATION
WITH YOUR OWN MOTHER.

14:42.542 --> 14:44.542
I THINK THE PROBLEM
IS THE VERY NOTION

14:44.542 --> 14:47.208
OF HAVING TO MAKE
CONVERSATION.

14:47.208 --> 14:50.625
EVERYTHING SEEMS TO BE
HAPPENING A LITTLE
TOO LATE, DOESN'T IT?

14:50.625 --> 14:54.542
I MEAN, WHY DID JEN
CALL ME OUT HERE NOW?

14:54.542 --> 14:56.458
WHY HAVE WE WAITED SO LONG?

14:56.458 --> 14:59.750
ONE THING I'VE LEARNED
IS TO REGRET THE PAST
IS USELESS.

14:59.750 --> 15:00.917
YOU CAN'T CHANGE IT.

15:00.917 --> 15:02.792
MIGHT AS WELL LIVE
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE

15:02.792 --> 15:05.667
AS PLEASANTLY
AS POSSIBLE.

15:05.667 --> 15:07.375
MOM, YOU'VE GONE SOFT.

15:07.375 --> 15:08.542
NEVER.

15:08.542 --> 15:11.625
NO, IT'S NICE.

15:11.625 --> 15:13.000
I THINK JEN'S
MADE YOU HAPPY.

15:16.250 --> 15:18.333
SHE SEEMS YOUNGER NOW
THAN SHE DID

15:18.333 --> 15:20.083
WHEN SHE WAS IN NEW YORK,

15:20.083 --> 15:23.083
RUNNING AROUND
LIKE A GROWNUP--

15:23.083 --> 15:25.667
A TOXIC ONE,
BUT A GROWNUP, NONETHELESS.

15:28.041 --> 15:30.583
IF SHE HAD STAYED THERE,
GOING THE WAY SHE WAS GOING...

15:32.708 --> 15:34.458
SHE WOULD HAVE RUN
RIGHT OVER ME, MOM.

15:35.708 --> 15:42.083
OH, HELEN. IT WASN'T
A MAGICAL TRANSFORMATION.

15:42.083 --> 15:43.625
SHE JUST NEEDED
A LITTLE PATIENCE

15:43.625 --> 15:47.083
AND, UM, NO ACCESS
TO PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION.

15:47.083 --> 15:48.750
HMM.

15:48.750 --> 15:52.083
MM, IT'S FUNNY.

15:52.083 --> 15:56.041
NOW THAT SHE
DOESN'T NEED ME,

15:56.041 --> 15:57.750
KINDA THINK
THAT I NEED HER.

15:57.750 --> 16:01.792
NOT AS MUCH
AS I NEEDED YOU, THOUGH.

16:01.792 --> 16:04.625
I COULD--I COULD
NEVER REPAY YOU.

16:05.708 --> 16:12.625
ACTS OF LOVE DO NOT
REQUIRE REPAYMENT.

16:12.625 --> 16:14.041
I MEAN, WHAT IF I NEEDED
TO CALL UPON YOU

16:14.041 --> 16:16.625
AND--AND I NEEDED
YOUR HELP, YOUR SUPPORT?

16:16.625 --> 16:18.208
YOU'D BE THERE FOR ME,
WOULDN'T YOU?

16:18.208 --> 16:20.917
