20:36.208 --> 20:38.000
NOT TALKING TO YOU.

20:40.708 --> 20:42.375
MAYBE IT SEEMED
LIKE IT WAS.

20:42.375 --> 20:45.375
AND I GUESS IT JUST...
BECAME ROUTINE,

20:45.375 --> 20:49.834
JUST ANOTHER THING
THAT I DIDN'T DO.

20:49.834 --> 20:54.834
WELL, LIKE SHOOTING HEROIN
OR DRIVING DRUNK.

20:54.834 --> 20:55.917
WOW, I'M UP THERE
WITH THE DANGEROUS
ACTIVITIES.

20:55.917 --> 20:57.542
OR CASUAL SEX.

20:59.917 --> 21:02.375
DAWSON, FOR SO LONG,
YOU WERE THE ONLY PERSON

21:02.375 --> 21:05.708
IN THE WHOLE WORLD
I WANTED TO BE WITH.

21:05.708 --> 21:09.375
THEN SOMEHOW YOU BECAME
MY ONLY ONE-NIGHT STAND.

21:09.375 --> 21:11.041
I NEVER MEANT
FOR IT TO BE LIKE THAT.

21:11.041 --> 21:11.875
I KNOW.

21:11.875 --> 21:13.542
I KNOW.

21:16.375 --> 21:18.500
MAYBE BEING IN THIS ROOM
MAKES IT EASIER.

21:22.583 --> 21:24.583
HAVING IT SET UP
THIS WAY,

21:24.583 --> 21:26.000
YOU KNOW,
I'M SO FAMILIAR, AND...

21:26.000 --> 21:31.333
SEEMS INSANE NOT TO TALK.

21:31.333 --> 21:33.834
AND SOMETIMES
THE HARDEST THINGS TO SAY

21:33.834 --> 21:35.083
ARE THE THINGS THAT...

21:38.083 --> 21:40.333
REALLY MATTER.

21:40.333 --> 21:42.583
HMM.

21:42.583 --> 21:44.125
WHY DO YOU THINK
I'VE SPENT YEARS

21:44.125 --> 21:45.583
TRYING TO WRITE
AN ENTIRE SCREENPLAY
ABOUT YOU?

21:48.000 --> 21:50.125
I READ IT IN ONE SITTING.
OK.

21:50.125 --> 21:51.000
I HOPE YOU DON'T THINK
THAT I GAVE IT TO YOU

21:51.000 --> 21:53.125
SO THAT
YOU COULD JUST SAY

21:53.125 --> 21:54.500
ALL THE OBLIGATORY
NICE THINGS.

21:54.500 --> 21:56.250
AND WHY WOULD I
FEEL OBLIGATED?

21:56.250 --> 21:58.500
EXACTLY, BECAUSE IF I CAN'T
GET AN HONEST OPINION

21:58.500 --> 22:00.500
FROM THE GIRL
WHO LOATHES ME MORE THAN
ANYONE ELSE IN THE WORLD,

22:00.500 --> 22:01.542
WHO CAN I TRUST, RIGHT?

22:01.542 --> 22:04.000
YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN
THIS DEVILISHLY CLEVER.

22:04.000 --> 22:06.625
WELL...

22:06.625 --> 22:07.792
YEAH.

22:07.792 --> 22:08.959
BUT...

22:10.959 --> 22:12.166
UH, I GOT--I GOT--

22:12.166 --> 22:13.792
I WANTED YOU
TO READ IT BECAUSE...

22:16.667 --> 22:18.834
WELL, YOU'RE REALLY
THE ONLY PERSON
IN THE WORLD

22:18.834 --> 22:21.458
WHO CAN TELL ME IF I
GOT IT RIGHT THIS TIME.

22:24.834 --> 22:26.583
YOU GREW UP, DAWSON.

22:28.875 --> 22:30.583
YOU GREW UP.

22:34.458 --> 22:36.750
I ALWAYS WANTED
TO THINK THAT YOU WERE
THIS HOPELESS DREAMER

22:36.750 --> 22:39.583
AND I WAS THE ADULT
THAT ESCAPED.

22:42.708 --> 22:44.375
BUT I DIDN'T ESCAPE
ANYTHING, NOT REALLY.

22:44.375 --> 22:47.000
SURE YOU DID.
YOU GOT OUT OF CAPESIDE.

22:47.000 --> 22:48.125
WASN'T THAT
THE ORIGINAL PLAN?

22:51.166 --> 22:53.625
COULDN'T ESCAPE MYSELF,
COULD I?

22:53.625 --> 22:55.291
YOU WERE RIGHT.

22:56.708 --> 22:59.000
SO MUCH OF WHAT
I WAS FIGHTING
WAS GROWING UP.

23:02.667 --> 23:06.083
AND I FIGURED OUT
THIS PAST YEAR
THAT IT'S HARD FOR ME...

23:08.625 --> 23:10.542
TO TALK ABOUT SEX,
TO TALK ABOUT...

23:11.375 --> 23:13.750
GETTING CLOSE WITH SOMEONE.

23:15.583 --> 23:17.583
AND MAYBE...

23:17.583 --> 23:18.708
I'M NOT SUPPOSED
TO LOSE MYSELF.

23:20.375 --> 23:25.417
NOW IT'S NOT PART
OF THE PLAN.

23:25.417 --> 23:27.708
BUT THEN AGAIN,
I NEVER THOUGHT
THAT LOSING YOU

23:27.708 --> 23:29.083
WAS PART
OF THE PLAN, EITHER.

23:29.083 --> 23:31.750
I THINK SOMETIMES...

23:32.834 --> 23:35.208
YOU HAVE TO LOSE
SOMEBODY COMPLETELY

23:35.208 --> 23:37.250
BEFORE YOU CAN
FIGURE OUT WHAT THEY
REALLY MEAN TO YOU.

23:40.583 --> 23:42.333
I MISSED YOU, JOE.

23:48.166 --> 23:50.417
YOU GOT IT RIGHT
THIS TIME, DAWSON.

23:56.250 --> 23:58.500
I MISSED US.

24:09.500 --> 24:12.583
SO HOW DID
YOU AND JENNIFER MEET?

24:12.583 --> 24:17.291
OH, NO, I'M--I'M JACK,
MRS. LINDLEY.

24:17.291 --> 24:18.583
WELL, YES, I KNOW THAT.

24:18.583 --> 24:21.125
YEAH, WELL,
T-THIS IS, UM,

24:21.125 --> 24:22.792
THIS IS JEN'S
BOYFRIEND HERE.

24:22.792 --> 24:24.125
OH, I'M SORRY.
YOU'RE NOT...

24:24.125 --> 24:25.625
NO, NO.
I'M--I'M THE GAY ONE.

24:27.166 --> 24:29.959
ACTUALLY WE, UM--
WE MET A FEW YEARS BACK.

24:29.959 --> 24:31.625
