NOT VERY DESCRIPTIVE.

24:47.792 --> 24:52.458
WELL, YOU AND JACK
ARE BOTH SO ATTRACTIVE,

24:52.458 --> 24:56.625
AND I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THE GAYS LOOK LIKE
THESE DAYS.

24:56.625 --> 24:58.750
THANK YOU?

24:58.750 --> 25:00.208
ARE YOU GOING TO SCHOOL
IN NEW YORK?

25:00.208 --> 25:01.625
YES, UH,
LEAVING TOMORROW ACTUALLY.

25:01.625 --> 25:03.125
WELL, YOU'LL HAVE
TO CALL ME.

25:03.125 --> 25:04.458
I KNOW LOTS
OF YOUNG PEOPLE

25:04.458 --> 25:05.708
WHO COULD TAKE YOU
OUT ON THE TOWN.

25:05.708 --> 25:09.083
THE PARKERS, WHO LIVE
DOWNSTAIRS FROM ME,

25:09.083 --> 25:09.750
HAVE
2 LOVELY DAUGHTERS...

25:09.750 --> 25:11.000
OK, MOM, THAT'S ENOUGH.

25:11.000 --> 25:14.625
MY BOYFRIEND DOESN'T NEED
TO BE MEETING ANYONE LOVELY.

25:14.625 --> 25:16.333
IT'S NOT LIKE WE'RE
BREAKING UP OR ANYTHING

25:16.333 --> 25:17.291
OH, GOOD TO KNOW.

25:17.291 --> 25:19.083
WELL, I'VE ONLY
JUST FIGURED OUT NOW

25:19.083 --> 25:20.333
WHICH ONE
IS YOUR BOYFRIEND.

25:20.333 --> 25:22.083
WELL, THAT'S
BECAUSE JACK ACTS
LIKE A BOYFRIEND.

25:22.083 --> 25:25.333
WELL, TECHNICALLY,
TECHNICALLY,
I AM HER BOYFRIEND.

25:25.333 --> 25:26.750
TECHNICALLY,
YOU'RE NOT MY BOYFRIEND.

25:26.750 --> 25:27.834
YOU DON'T
SLEEP WITH ME.

25:27.834 --> 25:29.333
IS THAT
THE ONLY DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN US?

25:29.333 --> 25:30.792
LOOK, WHO'S LEAVING ME
FOR HIGHER LEARNING
TOMORROW?

25:30.792 --> 25:32.834
HEY, COME ON. YOU SAID
YOU WERE HAPPY FOR ME.

25:32.834 --> 25:34.667
I AM, BUT DON'T BEGRUDGE
ME THE ONLY FRIEND

25:34.667 --> 25:36.250
THAT I HAVE LEFT
IN YOUR ABSENCE.

25:36.250 --> 25:37.792
JEN, YOU WERE
ALWAYS SO POPULAR.

25:37.792 --> 25:38.708
I KNOW. THAT WAS CALLED
PUTTING OUT, MOM.

25:43.375 --> 25:47.542
EVIE, YOU GET
YOUR BUTT OUT HERE.

25:47.542 --> 25:48.792
UNCLE BILL, WHAT ARE YOU--
WHAT ARE YOU--

25:48.792 --> 25:49.708
HEY, HEY, COOL IT.

25:49.708 --> 25:51.875
I GOT SOME BUSINESS
WITH THIS SKIRT,

25:51.875 --> 25:53.750
AND I'M NOT LEAVING
TILL IT'S FINISHED.

25:53.750 --> 25:54.708
EVIE!

25:54.708 --> 25:56.041
DO YOU KNOW THIS MAN?

25:56.041 --> 25:57.250
YEAH, HE'S C.J.'s
UNCLE BILL.

25:57.250 --> 25:59.083
HE--HE AND GRAMS
HAD A THING.

25:59.083 --> 26:00.750
A THING?

26:03.333 --> 26:05.625
WILLIAM, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

26:05.625 --> 26:08.708
NOW LOOK, YOU JUST
DON'T WALK AWAY
FROM BILL BRAXTON

26:08.708 --> 26:11.583
AND EXPECT HIM
TO ROLL OVER
LIKE A DEAD DOG.

26:11.583 --> 26:13.583
I'VE BEEN DOING
SOME P.I. WORK ON YOU,

26:13.583 --> 26:16.250
AND YOU KNOW
WHAT I FOUND OUT?

26:16.250 --> 26:18.542
YOU ARE FULL OF MALARKEY.

26:18.542 --> 26:21.542
BILL, THIS IS NEITHER
THE TIME OR THE PLACE
FOR THIS CONVERSATION.

26:21.542 --> 26:23.708
THAT'S HALF
YOUR PROBLEM RIGHT THERE.

26:23.708 --> 26:28.208
YOU KEEP WANTING
TO COMPARTMENTALIZE
EVERYTHING IN TIME AND SPACE,

26:28.208 --> 26:32.125
AND YOU'RE MAKING
YOURSELF SICK, AND THAT'S
WHY YOU HAVE CANCER,

26:32.125 --> 26:33.542
AND YOU'RE EATING
YOURSELF UP.

26:36.917 --> 26:38.625
MOM...

26:38.625 --> 26:41.250
IS THIS TRUE?

26:41.250 --> 26:42.959
YES.

26:45.083 --> 26:48.875
YES, HELEN, IT'S--
IT'S TRUE. UM...

26:48.875 --> 26:51.750
I--I CERTAINLY
NEVER INTENDED FOR YOU
TO FIND IT OUT THIS WAY.

26:51.750 --> 26:56.208
LOOK, I DON'T WANNA
WATCH ANOTHER WOMAN...

26:56.208 --> 26:58.834
WHO I LOVE, GIVE UP.

26:58.834 --> 27:02.875
WERE YOU SENT HERE
ON THIS EARTH TO DIE ALONE

27:02.875 --> 27:04.625
WITH YOUR KNITTING NEEDLES,

27:04.625 --> 27:06.083
OR WERE YOU SENT HERE
TO LIVE A LITTLE?

27:06.083 --> 27:09.625
YOU MUST HAVE
FAILED TO NOTICE
THAT I AM NOT ALONE.

27:09.625 --> 27:14.458
YES, I CAN SEE THERE ARE
A BUNCH OF PEOPLE HERE
WHO GIVE A DAMN,

27:14.458 --> 27:16.750
AND EVEN THOUGH
YOU SPURNED MY ADVANCES,

27:16.750 --> 27:18.959
I GIVE A DAMN, TOO.

27:22.625 --> 27:24.000
Jen: GRAMS...

27:24.000 --> 27:27.166
AREN'T YOU GONNA
THANK BILL FOR DOING
YOUR DIRTY WORK FOR YA?

27:27.166 --> 27:29.208
(SCOFFS)

27:29.208 --> 27:31.708
THANK YOU, JENNIFER.
I WAS JUST...

27:31.708 --> 27:32.500
ABOUT TO DO THAT.

27:32.500 --> 27:35.959
YOU MEAN,
NOBODY ELSE KNEW?

27:35.959 --> 27:38.625
NO, BILL,
NOBODY ELSE KNEW,

27:38.625 --> 27:41.500
WHICH ACCOUNTS
FOR THE SHOCK
ON MY DAUGHTER'S FACE.

27:41.500 --> 27:45.959
I--I--I GOTTA SAY, GRAMS,
I'M PRETTY SHOCKED, TOO.

27:45.959 --> 27:48.875
JEN, WHAT'S UP?
YOU WANNA TELL ME?

27:48.875 --> 27:51.291
Grams: JACK, IT WAS
NOT JENNIFER'S
RESPONSIBILITY

27:51.291 --> 27:53.000
TO TELL YOU.
IT WAS MINE.

27:53.000 --> 27:55.875
I'M SORRY.

27:55.875 --> 27:57.417
THIS IS WHY YOU CALLED ME?

27:57.417 --> 27:58.750
YEP.

27:58.750 --> 28:01.834
I--I DON'T KNOW.
GRAMS TOLD ME THAT
SHE HAD BREAST CANCER,

28:01.834 --> 28:04.834
AND IT--AND IT WAS JUST
LIKE THE WHOLE WORLD
MELTED AWAY,

28:04.834 --> 28:09.417
BUT I HAD A THOUSAND
QUESTIONS IN MY HEAD

28:09.417 --> 28:13.083
OF HOW AM I GOING TO
TAKE CARE OF HER
AND HOW LONG DO WE HAVE,

28:13.083 --> 28:16.208
AND, BILL,
I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

28:16.208 --> 28:19.875
I MEAN, GRAMS, YOU CAN'T
TRY AND BE A ROCK HERE,

28:19.875 --> 28:23.500
BECAUSE IT'S--IT'S NOT
MAKING YOU ANY HAPPIER
OR ANY BETTER,

28:23.500 --> 28:24.917
AND IT'S NOT MAKING
YOUR LIFE ANY EASIER,

28:24.917 --> 28:27.875
SO I--I JUST FEEL LIKE
THE BEST THING FOR YOU
TO DO RIGHT NOW

28:27.875 --> 28:31.041
IS JUST TO BE AROUND
YOUR FAMILY.

28:33.792 --> 28:34.875
I'M SO SORRY.

28:36.417 --> 28:39.041
WHAT CAN I DO?

28:39.041 --> 28:40.333
Jen: WELL...

28:40.333 --> 28:41.875
ACTUALLY,
IT'S FUNNY YOU SHOULD ASK

28:41.875 --> 28:44.375
BECAUSE I THINK THAT WE HAVE
KIND OF AN INTERESTING
OPPORTUNITY HERE.

28:44.375 --> 28:47.542
OPPORTUNITY FOR WHAT?

28:47.542 --> 28:50.000
TO MOVE TO NEW YORK
TO LIVE WITH MOM.

28:54.458 --> 28:56.542
I DON'T EVEN REALLY
WANNA FIGHT ABOUT IT
OR DISCUSS IT.

28:56.542 --> 28:58.166
I JUST WANT IT TO BE OK.

28:59.750 --> 29:03.291
OH, HELEN, I--I--
I COULDN'T DREAM OF...

29:03.291 --> 29:04.417
IMPOSING--

29:04.417 --> 29:06.708
Jen: NO, IT'S NOT.

29:06.708 --> 29:07.917
SHE LIVES 5 MINUTES AWAY

29:07.917 --> 29:10.875
FROM THE BEST HOSPITAL
IN THE COUNTRY.

29:10.875 --> 29:14.458
I DON'T SEE THAT THERE'S
ANY IMPOSITION IN THAT.

29:14.458 --> 29:15.458
BUT I--I--I--

29:15.458 --> 29:17.708
NO. MOM, IT'S OK.

29:18.458 --> 29:20.750
SHE'S RIGHT.

29:27.583 --> 29:29.792
I DIDN'T REALIZE
HOW LATE IT HAD GOTTEN.

29:29.792 --> 29:31.208
YEAH, WHEN YOU
CAME OVER HERE, YOU
PROBABLY DIDN'T EXPECT

29:31.208 --> 29:33.417
TO SPEND
THE WHOLE AFTERNOON
TALKIN', HUH?

29:33.417 --> 29:34.458
CALL IT A NICE SURPRISE.

29:34.458 --> 29:36.458
WELL, I'VE STILL GOT
ONE BIG PROBLEM, THOUGH.

29:36.458 --> 29:38.417
WHAT'S THAT?

29:38.417 --> 29:40.083
SAME ONE I'VE ALWAYS HAD,

29:40.083 --> 29:42.125
FINDING SOMEBODY
TO PLAY YOU.

29:49.375 --> 29:51.750
PACEY.

29:51.750 --> 29:53.917
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE HOME.

29:55.834 --> 29:57.625
WELL, I WASN'T REALLY
PLANNING ON MAKING A TRIP,

29:57.625 --> 29:59.500
BUT I NEEDED TO TALK
TO YOU FOR A SECOND.
IS THAT OK, DAWSON?

29:59.500 --> 30:00.959
YEAH, OF COURSE.

30:00.959 --> 30:05.291
I, UH--I GUESS
I'LL SEE YOU
TOMORROW MAYBE?

30:05.291 --> 30:06.291
DEAL.

30:06.291 --> 30:06.875
ALL RIGHT.

30:06.875 --> 30:07.959
ACTUALLY, JO, UM...

30:07.959 --> 30:10.375
WHY DON'T YOU
HANG OUT FOR A SECOND,

30:10.375 --> 30:12.500
'CAUSE YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO HEAR THIS
SOONER OR LATER ANYWAY.

30:12.500 --> 30:14.500
WHAT'S GOIN' ON?
ARE YOU OK?

30:17.125 --> 30:21.041
MAN, AND WE WERE JUST GETTIN'
BACK TO BE FRIENDS, TOO.
IT'S SUCH A SHAME TO RUIN THAT.

30:21.041 --> 30:22.500
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?
WHAT WOULD RUIN IT?

30:23.667 --> 30:26.583
MONEY. MONEY WOULD RUIN IT.

30:26.583 --> 30:31.166
W-WHAT HAPPENED?

30:31.166 --> 30:32.083
IT'S GONE.

30:32.083 --> 30:35.125
YOUR MONEY'S GONE,
MY MONEY'S GONE,

30:35.125 --> 30:37.834
SOME GUY ON LONG ISLAND'S
MONEY IS GONE--

30:37.834 --> 30:39.959
WHAT--WHAT
DO YOU MEAN GONE?

30:39.959 --> 30:42.667
THAT WAS ALL
THE MONEY THAT I HAD.

30:42.667 --> 30:43.792
I KNOW IT WAS, DAWSON,
AND I HONESTLY THOUGHT

30:43.792 --> 30:47.708
STEPATECH WAS GONNA
TAKE OFF, I SWEAR TO YOU.

30:47.708 --> 30:50.959
RIGHT. YEAH, O-OF COURSE.

30:50.959 --> 30:53.083
OTHERWISE WHY WOULD YOU
BLATANTLY IGNORE MY REQUEST
TO SELL THE STOCK?

30:53.083 --> 30:56.166
MAN, I WAS JUST TRYIN'
TO DO THE RIGHT THING.

30:56.166 --> 30:57.375
AH, DAMN IT, PACEY, THIS--

30:57.375 --> 31:00.875
(DAWSON SIGHS)

31:00.875 --> 31:02.458
YOU'RE ALWAYS TRYIN'
TO DO THE RIGHT THING.

31:02.458 --> 31:05.500
YOU'RE ALWAYS SO EAGER
TO BE THE HERO,

31:05.500 --> 31:08.708
YOU NEVER QUITE SEE
ALL THE PIECES
OF THE PUZZLE.

31:08.708 --> 31:10.834
Pacey: DAWSON...

31:10.834 --> 31:12.083
YOU CAME TO ME WITH YOUR DREAM

31:12.083 --> 31:14.041
BECAUSE YOU THOUGHT I COULD
HELP MAKE SOMETHING OF IT,

31:14.041 --> 31:17.875
AND SOMEHOW THIS COMES BACK
YET AGAIN TO THE FACT

31:17.875 --> 31:19.708
THAT I SCREWED YOU OVER?

31:19.708 --> 31:21.333
Joey: OK,
YOU KNOW WHAT, YOU TWO?

31:21.333 --> 31:23.333
LET'S JUST STICK
TO THE TOPIC AT HAND.

31:23.333 --> 31:26.417
OK, SO WE CAN JUST
SOLVE THIS PROBLEM

31:26.417 --> 31:30.625
BY GOING INSIDE
AND TRYING TO GET CALM...

31:30.625 --> 31:32.875
AND WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT.

31:32.875 --> 31:35.834
JOEY, TALKING
ABOUT THIS IS NOT
GONNA SOLVE ANYTHING.

31:35.834 --> 31:37.166
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

31:37.166 --> 31:40.667
HE MEANS
IT'S NOT ABOUT MONEY.

31:40.667 --> 31:43.875
SO FINE THEN, LET'S JUST
TALK ABOUT WHAT'S REALLY
GOIN' ON HERE.

31:43.875 --> 31:47.125
YOU KNOW WHAT? I SEE
NO REASON TO DRUDGE UP
BAGGAGE FROM THE PAST

31:47.125 --> 31:49.000
JUST TO FILL IN
THE MOMENT, PACEY.

31:49.000 --> 31:49.917
I MEAN,
LET'S REMEMBER SOMETHING.

31:49.917 --> 31:53.125
THIS EXCHANGE
BETWEEN YOU AND DAWSON

31:53.125 --> 31:54.708
IS PURELY
A BUSINESS EXCHANGE,

31:54.708 --> 31:57.208
AND I THINK
WE NEED TO REMEMBER
TO KEEP IT AT THAT.

31:57.208 --> 31:58.375
